description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a Head of Service of the Audiology Services at University Hospital of North Midlands NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Audiology services are delivered within a purpose built Hearing and Balance Centre and from community settings across North Staffordshire, serving a local population of over 460,000 and a specialist audiology service to a population of over 1 million.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and experienced Clinical Scientist to lead the team of highly skilled and competent staff. We provide a full range of adult and paediatric diagnostic and rehabilitative audiology including Direct referrals, Vestibular Assessment and Rehabilitation, Comprehensive Aural Rehabiltiation and ENT support. The department requires strategic leadership to ensure it continues its success within the AQP environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a BSc Hons Audiology or equivalent together with good communication, time management and IT skills. Ideally you should also have a post graduate managerial qualification, e.g. MBA, and have held a senior position within an Audiology Department for at least 2 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameShale LineJob titleDirectorate ManagerEmail addressshale.line@uhnm.nhs.ukTelephone number01782674343&lt;/p&gt;
